I stumbled across someone who was doing permanent makeup and was like , wow, this is so cool! Not only was I always interested in beauty and makeup but the amount of money I saw her make was shocking! 😎 So I went on a journey… and it changed my life! 

I went from hotel concierge to more money in a day than I made in a week. AND, I found a way to build a platform to help women feel better about themselves and be able to speak my mind, share my passions and create my own schedule to spend it how I wanted! 

🏆I started off just on the weekends on my days off and found help with my kids..in just a few weeks I saw I was really able to do it and here I am now sharing my secrets with you! 

🙌 Why, you ask? Well, first, yes I do make some money..but also I want to grow and I have found through growth not only financially but to actually live a fulfilled life giving back actually gives you a better feeling than anything in the world. It’s a Win, Win, Win.. I help you build your dream life, your helping me and we are helping our community.

Who would’ve thought your child hood traumas could stay with you your entire life?

Looking back and pondering on my “why did I do that’s?” I realize how much of an impact it really has on your every single day actions until you realize it…if that ever happens for you.

When I was younger I felt ugly because I had crooked teeth & my parents couldn’t afford braces. So I got them later in life. 

When I was younger I didn’t have the nicest of clothes because my parents couldn’t afford them. So I thought I was uglier than the ones who did. So I got them later in life. 

For so many years I just wanted to be accepted…without even realizing it. My actions proved it even as an adult… but how would’ve I known that?

The whole time I was trying to prove to the world I was worthy from childhood false lies I told myself. 

I’m so happy I discovered the TRUTH. That I was perfect the whole time❤️

Imagine an authentic power so true no one can disrupt your flow. 

You can tell me I’m not that great but guess what.. I wouldn’t hear you.
